Looks like the config screen resolves baseurl by calling "ServletUtils.getBaseUrl(request)"
{code}
    public GlobalJspContext(HttpServletRequest request,
                            FisheyeWebResourceManager webResourceManager, Collection<MessageSource> sources,
                            EffectiveUserProvider effectiveUserProvider, Mailer mailer) {
        this.request = request;

        this.webResourceManager = webResourceManager;
        this.sources = sources;
        this.effectiveUserProvider = effectiveUserProvider;
        this.mailer = mailer;

        siteUrl = ServletUtils.getBaseUrl(request);
        staticContextPath = request.getContextPath() + "/" + ActionDispatcherServlet.STATIC_DIR;
        threadName = Thread.currentThread().getName();
    }
{code}
while FeCruHostApplication does "RootConfig.getSiteURL()" :-
{code}
    @Override
    public URI getBaseUrl() {
        try {
            return new URI(rootConfig.getSiteURL());
        } catch (URISyntaxException e) {
            throw new RuntimeException("RootConfig.getSiteURL() is not a valid URI!"); // todo should reference config.xml
        }
    }
{code}

I'm not sure which one is right but they should be consistent. It is weird if the default is reported to be one thing on the admin page but something else gets published to external.

